<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen (but, according to the protologue, &quot;linea nigra marginatus&quot;). Thallus grey with tiny brown flecks, thinly epilithic, continuous. Perithecia 0.25-0.45 mm, 3/4-1-immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock; ca. 70-80 perithecia/cm2. Involucrellum covering half of the exciple, ca. 60-80 mm thick. Exciple ca. 0.25 mm in diam., wall black. Periphysoids ca. 35-50 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.5 mm. Ascospores 0-septate, 28-34(-38) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-13 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The studied specimen is tiny and better material is needed to solve the identity of the species. The specimen matches in most respects with 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subjunctiva" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subjunctiva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subjunctiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The spores seen were narrower, but the spore size given in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1950.10834796" author="Bouly de Lesdain, M" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe botanique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="169 - 171" refId="B3" refString="Bouly de Lesdain, M, 1950. Notes lichenologiques No. XXXV. Bulletin de la Societe botanique de France 97: 169 - 171, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1950.10834796" title="Notes lichenologiques No. XXXV." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1950.10834796" volume="97" year="1950">Bouly de Lesdain 1950</bibRefCitation>
) 25-33 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
13-16 mm is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subjunctiva" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subjunctiva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subjunctiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
